settings.name: max_science_pack
settings.description: The level of science pack required to reach your goal.

settings.name: goal
settings.description: Goal required to complete the game.

settings.name: tech_tree_layout
settings.description: How technology trees are laid out.

settings.name: min_tech_cost
settings.description: The cheapest a Technology can be in Science Packs.

settings.name: max_tech_cost
settings.description: The most expensive a Technology can be in Science Packs.

settings.name: tech_cost_distribution
settings.description: Random distribution of costs of the Science Packs.

values.name: even
values.description: Any number between min and max is equally likely.

values.name: low
values.description: Low costs, near the minimum, are more likely.

values.name: middle
values.description: Medium costs, near the average, are more likely.

values.name: high
values.description: High costs, near the maximum, are more likely.

settings.name: tech_cost_mix
settings.description: Percent chance that a preceding Science Pack is also required. Chance is rolled per preceding pack.

settings.name: ramping_tech_costs
settings.description: DOC ME

settings.name: silo
settings.description: This option can randomize the recipe to create the silo, or alternatively auto-spawn it.

settings.name: satellite
settings.description: This option can randomize the recipe to create the satellite.

settings.name: free_samples
settings.description: Whether you receive free items with technologies.

settings.name: tech_tree_information
settings.description: What information will be displayed in the tech tree

settings.name: recipe_time
settings.description: Randomize the amount of time it will take to craft things. This affects all crafting types. "New" options ignore the original time.

settings.name: recipe_ingredients
settings.description: Randomize ingredients for rocket and science pack, or rocket only.

settings.name: imported_blueprints
settings.description: Whether blueprints from outside the current savegame are allowed.

settings.name: progressive
settings.description: Merges together Technologies like "automation-1" to "automation-3" into 3 copies of "Progressive Automation", which awards them in order.

settings.name: evolution_traps
settings.description: When these are researched, they will also progress enemy evolution.

settings.name: attack_traps
settings.description: Adds a trigger to certain items which will cause the enemy to attack your base when the item is received.

settings.name: evolution_trap_increase
settings.description: When an evolution trap is researched, the scale by which enemy evolution will be boosted. Increases scale down proportionally to the session's current evolution factor (40 increase at 0.50 will add 0.20... 40 increase at 0.75 will add 0.10...)

settings.name: energy_link
settings.description: Allow sending energy to other worlds. 25% of the energy is lost in the transfer.
